- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses an algorithm for solving the problem. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the paper involves finding minimum area triangles, which is a discrete optimization problem. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper proves a lower bound for the problem in the algebraic computation tree model. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is less likely but still possible as the paper involves finding optimal solutions to a geometric problem, which can be related to game theory.
